DIPHTHERIA - UKRAINE: (LUHANSK)
*******************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Fri 22 Jun 2018
Source: Siver Post [edited]
https://sivpost.com/ukraine-faces-an-outbreak-of-diphtheria-a-medical/3815/


Ukraine in 2018-2019 is threatened by an outbreak of diphtheria. [The 1st diphtheria case in Ukraine in 2018 was reported in January 2018 from Luhansk, https://112.international/society/first-diphtheria-case-in-ukraine-in-2018-reported-25140.html. - Mod.ML].

Secretary of the National Medical Chamber Sergey Kravchenko said: "Only one case creates an alert. Ukraine has already recorded 2 cases of diphtheria in the Luhansk region. We must pay tribute to the professionalism of doctors, as not in all cases were the cultures confirmed as diphtheria. This requires a serological laboratory test that is not conducted in Ukraine.

Accordingly, our physicians, are on time and have identified and localized the alert. Antibiotics for diphtheria will not help; it requires a specific serum, which is currently in the Ukraine. The US has alleged that India handed over 900 doses, but nobody knows whether this information is true. [In February 2018, Ukraine was reported to have only 900 doses of anti-diphtheria serum, https://www.kyivpost.com/ukraine-politics/bohomolets-says-ukraine-900-doses-anti-diphtheria-serum.html]. Ukraine, according to the WHO and our doctors, is in 2018-2019 threatened with an outbreak of diphtheria," Sergey Kravchenko said.

He stressed that in Ukraine over the last 3 years, there has been a failure [to vaccinate against] measles and diphtheria.

"Ukraine has moved on procurement of medicines through international organizations. The Health Ministry was unable to make an adequate request, and international organizations are unable to undertake adequate purchase. Diphtheria protection requires vaccination, but it does not give a 100% guarantee that the person will not get sick. However, vaccinated citizens tolerate this disease in less severe forms," - concluded Sergey Kravchenko.

Rubizhne, Luhansk oblast, had the 2nd case of diphtheria at the beginning of 2018.

--
